NATIONAL SURETY CORPORATION v. PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN, for the Use and Benefit of Stanley GABBARD, by William A. Gabbard, His Next Friend. No. 7765. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Dec. 8, 1937. Milton A. Behrendt and Mason, Davidson & Mansfield, all of Detroit, Mich., for appellant. Walter M. Nelson, of Detroit, Mich., for appellee.

Before MOORMAN, HICKS and SIMONS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be, and the same is, dismissed, pursuant to motion of appellant.
